The paper discusses compressive sensing and its application to diffraction tomography, which involves imaging of objects using scattered waves. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely sub-category as it deals with the theory of compressive sensing. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category as it involves image reconstruction. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category as it deals with signal processing and image compression. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible sub-category as it involves numerical methods for solving inverse problems. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be relevant if the paper discusses network-based approaches to compressive sensing.
